// ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// TNT OPENING DRIVE (OD) v2 — Extreme Anomaly Detection
// ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// CHANGELOG v1 → v2 (2026-05-04)
// ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//   1. DYNAMITE — FVG check now MANDATORY. v1 was a stdev-range filter only;
//      called itself "displacement" without FVG (Verification Protocol Rule 1
//      violation). Now: bar[1] AND bar[2] both exceed range threshold + same
//      direction + FAUNA on bar[1] AND bar[2] (per-candle, Protocol Rule 4) +
//      bar[0] confirms FVG. Offset = -1. Visual moves from bar[0] to bar[1].
//   2. UU / UUU / UUUU — added new qualification path "pG":
//        Counts distinct qualifier types present in streak from
//        {PBJ, DISP, FAUNA, SAAB, RVOL1x, GrandSlam}. Requires k ≥ streak-size
//        (UU=2, UUU=3, UUUU=4). Qualifiers can stack on the same bar; don't
//        need to be on every bar. ORs into existing pA/pB/pC/pE/pF — additive,
//        does not remove existing paths. (HV+D path pD intentionally skipped:
//        TNT OD has no HV+D engine; per Anish, not adding it here.)
//   3. Density 1/2/3 — plotshape offset 0 → -1. Chain touches Napalm which
//      has displacement+FVG. Per Protocol Rule 2, offset must be -1.
//   4. UU/UUU/UUUU + TNT ANY — plotshape offset 0 → -1. Same Rule 2 reason.
//   5. WBUSH detections added. Ports HEAVY PENTAGON's 5 Heavy Combo
//      classifications (Heavy Yin-Yang, Heavy Nagasaki, Heavy Nagasaki Vol,
//      Heavy Trident, Neutral Heavy x2) — bull / bear / neutral each. WBUSH
//      = any of the 15 fired. Three new plots:
//        WBUSH+TNTOD ANY Bull   (WBUSH-bull AND any TNTOD bull plot)
//        WBUSH+TNTOD ANY Bear   (WBUSH-bear AND any TNTOD bear plot)
//        WBUSH Neutral          (WBUSH-neutral standalone — alert worth
//                                knowing; classified neutral by HEAVY
//                                PENTAGON's own bull/bear/neutral logic)
//   6. NAGASAKI alert — now gated by checkbox, default OFF (was always-on).
//      Floods alerts otherwise. New UI group "★ NAGASAKI ALERT ★" at bottom.
//   7. Max TNT 1.0 Zones default 15 → 30. Max TNT 2.0 Zones default 8 → 30.
//      Matches B2B PUP scan-depth preference.
//   8. Tooltips added to every Tier 1, Tier 2, Density, UU, WBUSH input.bool().
//      Hover in TradingView settings now explains each detection.
// ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//
// ─── SIGNAL TAXONOMY & DEFINITIONS ──────────────────────────────────────────
//
// TERMINOLOGY:
//   TNT     = Three-engine confluence (VOB + ANISH + FLUX)
//   NPM     = Napalm — displacement through an active TNT zone
//   CONT    = Continuous — sudden-change proximity (rapid-fire events within N bars)
//   RET     = Return — price retraces back into a TNT zone after breakout
//   PBJ     = Supertrend-based entry engine (VWMA + ATR trailing stop)
//   CS1     = FVG Combo — consecutive or HV-backed fair-value gaps
//   FAUNA   = Candle anatomy qualifier (Momentum Bar, Range Expansion, Trend Accel, Gap & Go)
//   RVOL    = Relative volume rank (SAAB, 1x, GrandSlam tiers)
//   WMD     = Volume ratio rank (Pentagon, WTC, Hiroshima, Nagasaki tiers)
//   DISP    = Displacement — bar[1] range exceeds stdev threshold, bar[0] confirms FVG
//   ENR     = Enriched — co-signal from USE V5 engine (RVOL, WMD, FAUNA, CS1, PUP/PPD, HV1000, DYNAMITE)
//   HV      = High Volume rank — volume is highest in N-bar lookback (N = 50 to 1000)
//   FVG     = Fair Value Gap — price gap between bar[0] and bar[2] that bar[1] spans
//
// ─── TIER SYSTEM ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// TIER 1: Fires as-is. Multi-axis confluence already built into the combo.
//   B2B NAPALM       Back-to-back Napalm on consecutive visual bars.
//                    Detects: serial displacement through TNT zones.
//                    Axes: Price displacement + Zone (x2 consecutive).
//                    Offset: -1 (displacement+FVG in chain). Plot bar = bar[0]-1.
//
//   RC NPM+TNT       Rare Combo — Napalm and TNT fire on the same visual bar.
//                    Detects: displacement event coincides with structural confluence.
//                    Axes: Price displacement + Zone + Structural breakout.
//                    Offset: -1 (NPM is offset-1; TNT at [1] = same visual bar).
//
//   FUSE             Sequential NPM → TNT → CONT within proximity window.
//                    Detects: escalating event cascade in tight temporal cluster.
//                    Axes: Displacement + Structure + Temporal clustering.
//                    Offset: 0 (CONT has no displacement+FVG in its chain).
//
//   CATALYST         Napalm + CS1 on the same visual bar.
//                    Detects: displacement event backed by FVG clustering or HV-FVG.
//                    Axes: Price displacement + FVG structural confluence.
//                    Offset: -1 (both NPM and CS1 have displacement+FVG).
//
//   PBJ+NPM          PBJ crossover + Napalm on same visual bar.
//                    Detects: supertrend reversal coincides with zone displacement.
//                    Axes: Supertrend reversal + Displacement + Zone.
//                    Offset: -1 (NPM offset-1; PBJ at [1] = same visual bar).
//
//   PBJ+TNT          PBJ crossover + TNT on same visual bar.
//                    Detects: supertrend reversal coincides with structural confluence.
//                    Axes: Supertrend reversal + Structural breakout.
//                    Offset: 0 (neither has displacement+FVG in combo chain).
//
//   IGNITE TNT+CONT  TNT + Continuous on same visual bar.
//                    Detects: structural breakout that is also part of rapid-fire cluster.
//                    Axes: Structural breakout + Temporal clustering.
//                    Offset: 0 (TNT and CONT are both offset-0).
//
//   IGNITE NPM+CONT  Napalm + Continuous on same visual bar.
//                    Detects: displacement event that is also part of rapid-fire cluster.
//                    Axes: Displacement + Zone + Temporal clustering.
//                    Offset: -1 (NPM offset-1; CONT at [1] = same visual bar).
//
//   DYNAMITE         B2B extreme displacement + FAUNA on both consecutive bars.
//                    Detects: consecutive bars with extreme range AND strong candle anatomy.
//                    Axes: Serial displacement + Candle anatomy (x2).
//                    Offset: 0 (checks consecutive displaced bars, no FVG in combo chain).
//
// TIER 2: Hard-gated — NEVER fires without USE V5 enrichment co-signal.
//   TNT ENRICHED     TNT detection + enrichment on same bar.
//   NPM ENRICHED     Napalm detection + enrichment on visual bar.
//   CONT ENRICHED    Continuous detection + enrichment on same bar.
//   RC TNT+RET ENR   TNT + Return on same bar + enrichment.
//   RC RET+NPM ENR   Return + Napalm on same visual bar + enrichment.
//   PBJ+RET ENRICHED PBJ + Return on same bar + enrichment.
//
// OTHER:
//   DENSITY 1/2/3    Rolling window: X visual events within Y bars. Temporal density.
//   UU/UUU/UUUU+TNT  U-streak (consecutive qualified RVOL bars with path qualification)
//                    overlapping with any TNT indicator signal within the streak window.
//
// ─── OFFSET SUMMARY ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//   Offset -1: B2B NAPALM, RC NPM+TNT, CATALYST, PBJ+NPM, IGNITE NPM+CONT,
//              NPM ENRICHED, RC RET+NPM ENRICHED
//   Offset  0: Everything else
//
// ─── ALERT FORMAT ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//   DIRECTION | FIRST_STATUS | NAME
//   DIRECTION:    BULL or BEAR
//   FIRST_STATUS: FIRST !!! (first bar, gap ≤ bar range — price action is strong)
//                 FIRST XXX (first bar, gap > bar range — gap did heavy lifting)
//                 NOT !!!   (not the first bar of the session)
//   NEVER includes ticker, timeframe, or exchange (TradingView adds automatically).
//
// ─── MASTER TOGGLES ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//   First Bar Only:    When ON, alerts require first bar of session AND any HV rank
//                      (volume ≥ highest in 50-bar lookback) on the plot bar.
//                      Both conditions must be true. Alerts blocked if either missing.
//   Aggregate Alerts:  When ON, one combined alert per bar.
//                      When OFF, individual alerts per detection.
//
// ─── EXCEPTIONS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//   CHECKBOX BYPASSERS:    Nagasaki (fires standalone alert without a toggle).
//   AGGREGATOR BYPASSERS:  Nagasaki (excluded from the aggregated alert string).
//
// ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

//@version=5
indicator("TNT Opening Drive OD v2 (tick-safe)", "TNT OD v2", overlay = true,
     max_lines_count = 500, max_labels_count = 500, max_boxes_count = 500, max_bars_back=2500)

// ═══ TICK-SAFE SHIM ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// Replaces time("D") and tv_ta.relativeVolume() — both throw RE10023 on tick
// charts. See tick-compatible/README.md for the full conversion contract.
_dayKey() => year * 10000 + month * 100 + dayofmonth
_rvol(simple int length, simple bool cumulative) =>
    bool _isNew = ta.change(_dayKey()) != 0
    var float _cum = 0.0
    _cum := (_isNew or bar_index == 0) ? volume : _cum + volume
    float _cur = cumulative ? _cum : volume
    float _avg = ta.sma(_cur, math.max(length, 1))
    [_cur, _avg, _isNew]
// ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// ─── MASTER ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
grpM = "★ MASTER ★"
bool masterFirstBar  = input.bool(true, "First Bar Only Alerts", group = grpM,
     tooltip = "When ON, alerts require first bar of session AND any HV rank (vol ≥ highest in 50 bars) on the plot bar.")
bool masterAggregate = input.bool(true, "Aggregate Alerts", group = grpM,
     tooltip = "When ON, one combined alert per bar. When OFF, individual alerts per detection.")

